snippet.textDisplay:
Im playing lies of pi for the first time right now and its extremely boring and the maps are absolute basic minimum. And map design looks bad too, compared to map design of lords of the fallen its like utter trash.
Most of the enemies are just like the enemies of the start area. I kill like 10 enemies with r1 spam and walk like 10 minutes and finish one map. Thats simply ridiculous.
And then i have to return to the base everytime to level up my character. Peak stupidity.
Boss fights are bad and only difficult because of the untelegraphed attacks.
The idea with the puppets is very cool, but its poorly implemented.
I cant understand why this game had so much hype and good ratings.
Its the first boring soulsgames ive played.
Idk how far in the story i am (act VI Rosa street), but no other souls game had so boring maps and gameplay.
Maybe the game will get drastically better, but i doubt it and it would still make the first part of the game very bad.
Never trust on peoples ratings, most of them are completely clueless.

snippet.textDisplay: Unbelievable! It's so beautiful. The wait is coming to an end and I have so many questions: Will we really meet the legendary stalker? What will she say when she sees P, friend or foe? Was that the real Alidoro? Does the story start after the victory over the Archbishop? So that we use the golden Stargazer and travel to another part of Krat? Or do we jump even further back in time to the beginning of the year, when there was still snow and Spring was a baby? Because P's story doesn't start until autumn? Or is this the future and we see Spring's children, but didn't they say it was a prequel? Who is the woman with the flying puppet behind her? Is she the new endboss? Where is Geppetto? ....? So many questions.
